comment.narrative:
- Completion of the conversion process of all foam sandwish panels manufacturers (4) and Air conditioning enterprises (2);
- Monitoring the conversion of 1 foam and 1 air conditioning enterprises that were completed in 2017;
- Initiationof the reconversion process at the solar and electrical water heaters enterprises (13);
- Initiation of activities addressing the RAC sectors through building their technical capacities (workshops, training programs, certification of technicians, supply of equipment to vocational school, ... etc.);
- Initiation of activities related to the HPMP Stage-II, tranche-2 budget (US$ 1,114,000);
- The phase-out of around 45% of the aggregate HCFCs baseline (approximately 33 ODP Tons) by end of 2019;
- Preparation of performance verification report of the annual implementation plan for the year 2018 (to be submitted for consideration in the 83rd ExCom meeting);
- Preparation of a demonstration project in the refrigeration sector (a supermarket) converting their refrigerating system to a Carbon Dioxide refrigerant technology. The fund will be provided through UNDP MPU.

Project:
- Monitoring the completion of the conversion process of (4) foam sandwish panels manufacturers and (2) Air conditioning enterprises;
- UNIC (Air Conditioning Enterprise): Completion of Milestone-2 (Purchase of equipment and tools for the conversion) and Milestone 3 (Final and complete conversion) will be submitted before end of 2019;
- Postpone the initiation of the reconversion of 12 Solar and Electrical Water Heaters (SWH) due to lack of technology availability, coordination meetings to discuss their implementation conversion plans as per the technologies available in the national and international market i.e. Methyle formate or HFO;
- Activities addressing the Refrigeration and Air Conditioning (RAC) sector through: purchase of equipment for Dekwaneh Vocational School, Training programmes for teachers at Vocational Schools, coordination with the RAC enterprises (manufacturing and servicing) on alternative technologies available in the market (HCs) as well as providing technical assistance for importers on alternatives for R-141b usage for flushing in RAC systems;
-HPMP Stage-II tranche 2 budget: completion of activities in 2019 (conversion of 1 AC industry, inauguration of 1 RAC training center etc..) and the remaining activities will be completed as planned in 2020;
-Prepared the work plan for the RAC servicing sector 2020-2022;
- Postpone the preparation of the performance verification report to 2020 to report on the 2019 annual implementation year to be submitted for the 84th Executive Committee Meeting, as per our discussion with the Multilateral Fund through UNDP;
- The demonstration project in the refrigeration sector conversion of a supermarket to Carbon Dioxide refrigerant technology was not approved due to the delay in Ratifying Kigali Amendment;
Agreements, Laws, Decrees and Decisions:
- The phase-out of 40% was achieved of the aggregate HCFCs baseline (approximately 29 ODP Tons) by end of 2019

